description:
Research the 'Rate of Onset' and 'Persistence' properties for five hazardous chemicals on CAMEO Chemicals (https://cameochemicals.noaa.gov/) to create a casualty triage support report. Analyze Phosgene (CAS 75-44-5), Hydrogen Cyanide (CAS 74-90-8), Chlorine (CAS 7782-50-5), Sulfuric Acid (CAS 7664-93-9), and Nitrogen Dioxide (CAS 10102-44-0). For each chemical, classify the Triage Category as 'IMMEDIATE' if the onset is described as Immediate, Rapid, or Minutes, and 'DELAYED' if described as Delayed, Hours, or Latent. Create a JSON file at ~/Documents/triage_classification.json with the following structure:

[
  {
    "chemical": "Chemical Name",
    "rate_of_onset": "extracted text",
    "persistence": "extracted text",
    "triage_category": "IMMEDIATE|DELAYED"
  }
]
